{
  "texts": [
    "The authors test the proposed approach on a dataset that considers both real-world and synthetic data and assess the prediction accuracy using the MAPE.",
    "Also, they evaluate the performance of the proposed approach through energy cost savings, relative savings, episodic rewards, and value distribution.",
    "This work tackles the problem of controlling an Energy Storage System in a microgrid with its demand, RES, and dynamic energy pricing to perform energy arbitrage and improve the use of RES leading to reduced energy cost.",
    "Finally, the authors point out the limited availability of data that requires an efficient algorithm training procedure.",
    "A key aspect of sustainability and cost-effectiveness in grid operation is optimal energy dispatch."
  ]
}